<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Shane Duffy scored a dramatic late equaliser as the Republic of Ireland drew 1-1 with Bulgaria in Stephen Kenny's first game in charge. </p>

<p>Bozhidar Kraev put Bulgaria ahead with a neat finish in the 56th minute of the Nations League clash.</p>

<p>However, Duffy, who recently signed for Celtic on loan from Brighton, ensured Ireland got a point with a header.  </p>

<p>Next up for Ireland is a home game against Finland on Sunday.</p>

<p>More to follow... </p>

